President Biden met with Prime Minister Kishida Fumio of Japan and President Yoon Suk Yeol of the Republic of Korea in Hiroshima, Japan. He praised their efforts to enhance bilateral ties and acknowledged that their work has strengthened the trilateral partnership and the Indo-Pacific region. The leaders discussed ways to further elevate their trilateral cooperation, particularly in addressing the nuclear and missile threats posed by the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), economic security, and their respective Indo-Pacific Strategies.